WEBVTT

00:20.540 --> 00:26.720
Then he called his twelve disciples together, and gave them power and authority over all

00:26.720 --> 00:32.320
devils, and to cure diseases. And he sent them to preach the kingdom of God, and to

00:32.320 --> 00:39.040
heal the sick. And he said unto them, Take nothing for your journey, neither staves nor

00:39.040 --> 00:45.020
scrip, neither bread, neither money, neither have two coats apiece, and whatsoever house

00:45.020 --> 00:52.860
ye enter into, there abide, and thence depart. And whosoever will not receive you, when ye

00:52.860 --> 00:58.460
go out of that city, shake off the very dust from your feet for a testimony against them.

00:59.340 --> 01:04.040
And they departed, and went through the towns, preaching the gospel, and healing everywhere.

01:05.140 --> 01:11.660
Now Herod the Tetrarch heard of all that was done by him, and he was perplexed, because

01:11.660 --> 01:17.540
that it was said of some that John was risen from the dead, and of some that Elias had

01:17.540 --> 01:25.040
and of others that one of the old prophets was risen again. And Herod said, John have

01:25.040 --> 01:32.440
I beheaded, but who is this of whom I hear such things? And he desired to see him. And

01:32.440 --> 01:37.480
the apostles, when they were returned, told him all that they had done, and he took them

01:37.480 --> 01:43.960
and went aside privately into a desert place belonging to the city called Bethsaida. And

01:43.960 --> 01:48.480
the people, when they knew it, followed him. And he received them, and spake unto them

01:48.480 --> 01:54.260
of the kingdom of God, and healed them that had need of healing. And when the day began

01:54.260 --> 02:00.160
to wear away, then came the twelve, and said unto him, Send the multitude away, that they

02:00.160 --> 02:06.220
may go into the towns, and country round about, and lodge, and get vigils, for we are here

02:06.220 --> 02:13.440
in a desert place. But he said unto them, Give ye them to eat. And they said, We have

02:13.440 --> 02:18.840
no more but five loaves and two fishes, except we should go and buy meat for all this people.

02:19.540 --> 02:25.400
For they were about five thousand men. And he said to his disciples, Make them sit down

02:25.400 --> 02:32.920
by fifties in a company. And they did so, and made them all sit down. Then he took the

02:32.920 --> 02:38.640
five loaves and the two fishes, and looking up to heaven he blessed them and break, and

02:38.640 --> 02:45.000
gave to the disciples to set before the multitude. And they did eat, and were all filled, and

02:45.000 --> 02:51.280
there was taken up of fragments that remained to them twelve baskets. And it came to pass,

02:51.300 --> 02:56.280
as he was alone praying, his disciples were with him, and he asked them, saying, Whom

02:56.280 --> 03:03.720
say the people that I am? They answering said, John the Baptist. But some say, Elias, and

03:03.720 --> 03:09.840
others say, that one of the old prophets is risen again. And he said unto them, But whom

03:09.840 --> 03:18.700
say ye that I am? Peter answering said, The Christ of God. And he straightly charged

03:18.700 --> 03:23.940
them and commanded them to tell no man that thing, saying, The son of man must suffer

03:23.940 --> 03:30.200
many things, and be rejected of the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be slain,

03:30.200 --> 03:37.280
and be raised the third day. And he said to them all, If any man will come after me, let

03:37.280 --> 03:43.520
him deny himself, and take up his cross daily, and follow me. For whosoever will save his

03:43.520 --> 03:48.980
life shall lose it. But whosoever will lose his life for my sake, the same shall save

03:48.980 --> 03:55.400
it. For what is a man advantaged if he gain the whole world, and lose himself, or be cast

03:55.400 --> 04:02.100
away? For whosoever shall be ashamed of me, and of my words, of him shall the son of man

04:02.100 --> 04:07.600
be ashamed, when he shall come in his own glory, and in his father's, and of the holy

04:07.600 --> 04:13.120
angels. But I tell you of a truth, there be some standing here, which shall not taste

04:13.120 --> 04:19.780
of death, till they see the kingdom of God. And it came to pass, about an eight days after

04:19.780 --> 04:24.900
these sayings, he took Peter and John and James, and went up into a mountain to pray.

04:25.580 --> 04:32.500
And as he prayed, the fashion of his countenance was altered, and his raiment was white and

04:32.500 --> 04:38.160
glistering. And behold, there talked with him two men, which were Moses and Elias, who

04:38.160 --> 04:44.760
appeared in glory, and spake of his decease, which he should accomplish at Jerusalem. But

04:44.760 --> 04:49.460
Peter and they that were with him were heavy with sleep, and when they were awake, they

04:49.460 --> 04:55.680
saw his glory, and the two men that stood with him. And it came to pass, as they departed

04:55.680 --> 05:01.280
from him, Peter said unto Jesus, Master, it is good for us to be here, and let us make

05:01.280 --> 05:07.180
three tabernacles, one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias, not knowing what

05:07.180 --> 05:13.200
he said. While he thus spake, there came a cloud, and overshadowed them, and they feared

05:13.200 --> 05:18.320
as they entered into the cloud. And there came a voice out of the cloud saying, This

05:18.320 --> 05:25.460
is my beloved son, hear him. And when the voice was passed, Jesus was found alone, and

05:25.460 --> 05:31.080
they kept it close, and told no man in those days any of those things which they had seen.

05:31.980 --> 05:36.620
And it came to pass, that on the next day, when they were come down from the hill, much

05:36.620 --> 05:43.120
people met him. And behold, a man of the company cried out, saying, Master, I beseech thee,

05:43.420 --> 05:50.420
look upon my son, for he is mine only child. And lo, a spirit taketh him, and he suddenly

05:50.420 --> 05:56.420
crieth out, and it teareth him, that he foameth again, and bruising him, hardly departeth

05:56.420 --> 06:02.640
from him. And I besought thy disciples to cast him out, and they could not. And Jesus

06:02.640 --> 06:10.000
answering said, O faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I be with you, and suffer you?

06:10.320 --> 06:18.240
Bring thy son hither. And as he was yet a-coming, the devil threw him down, and tear him. And

06:18.240 --> 06:23.460
Jesus rebuked the unclean spirit, and healed the child, and delivered him again to his

06:23.460 --> 06:29.640
father. And they were all amazed at the mighty power of God. But while they wondered every

06:29.640 --> 06:36.060
one at all things which Jesus did, he said unto his disciples, Let these sayings sink

06:36.060 --> 06:42.420
down into your ears, for the Son of man shall be delivered into the hands of men. But they

06:42.420 --> 06:47.180
understood not this saying, and it was hid from them, that they perceived it not, and

06:47.180 --> 06:53.580
they feared to ask him of that saying. Then there arose a reasoning among them, which

06:53.580 --> 06:59.480
of them should be the greatest. And Jesus, perceiving the thought of their heart, took

06:59.480 --> 07:04.800
a child, and set him by him, and said unto them, Whosoever shall receive this child in

07:04.800 --> 07:11.480
thy name, receiveth me. And whosoever shall receive me, receiveth him that sent me. For

07:11.480 --> 07:18.660
he that is least among you all, the same shall be great. And John answered, and said, Master,

07:18.680 --> 07:24.660
we saw one casting out devils in thy name, and we forbade him, because he followeth not

07:24.660 --> 07:31.240
with us. And Jesus said unto him, Forbid him not, for he that is not against us, is for

07:31.240 --> 07:37.760
us. And it came to pass, when the time was come, that he should be received up, he steadfastly

07:37.760 --> 07:43.280
set his face to go to Jerusalem, and sent messengers before his face, and they went,

07:43.680 --> 07:49.660
and entered into a village of the Samaritans, to make ready for him. And they did not receive

07:49.660 --> 07:56.360
him, because his face was as though he would go to Jerusalem. And when his disciples, James

07:56.360 --> 08:01.360
and John saw this, they said, Lord, wilt thou that we command fire to come down from

08:01.360 --> 08:07.080
heaven and consume them, even as Elias did? But he turned, and rebuked them, and said,

08:07.720 --> 08:13.680
Ye know not what manner of spirit ye are of. For the Son of man is not come to destroy

08:13.680 --> 08:19.640
men's lives, but to save them. And they went to another village, and it came to pass, that,

08:19.920 --> 08:25.860
as they went in the way, a certain man said unto him, Lord, I will follow thee whithersoever

08:25.860 --> 08:33.260
thou goest. And Jesus said unto them, Foxes have holes, and birds of the air have nests,

08:33.680 --> 08:41.600
but the Son of man hath not where to lay his head. And he said unto another, Follow me.

08:41.880 --> 08:48.280
But he said, Lord, suffer me first to go and bury my father. Jesus said unto him, Let the

08:48.280 --> 08:54.540
dead bury their dead, but go thou and preach the kingdom of God. And another also said,

08:54.540 --> 08:59.940
Lord, I will follow thee, but let me first go bid them farewell, which are at home at

08:59.940 --> 09:06.600
my house. And Jesus said unto him, No man, having put his hand to the plow, and looking

09:06.600 --> 09:11.980
back, is fit for the kingdom of God. Chapter 10

09:12.980 --> 09:17.640
After these things the Lord appointed other seventy also, and sent them two and two before

09:17.640 --> 09:24.380
his face into every city and place, whether he himself would come. Therefore said he unto

09:24.380 --> 09:30.840
them, The harvest truly is great, but the laborers are few. Pray ye therefore the Lord

09:30.840 --> 09:37.880
of the harvest that he would send forth laborers into his harvest. Go your ways. Behold I send

09:37.880 --> 09:44.320
you forth as lambs among wolves, carrying neither purse nor scrip nor shoes, and salute

09:44.320 --> 09:51.500
no man by the way. And into whatsoever house ye enter first say, Peace be to this house.

09:51.500 --> 09:58.180
And if the Son of Peace be there, your peace shall rest upon it. If not, it shall turn

09:58.180 --> 10:04.820
to you again. And in the same house remain eating and drinking such things as they give,

10:05.240 --> 10:11.320
for the laborer is worthy of his hire. Go not from house to house. And into whatsoever

10:11.320 --> 10:17.620
city ye enter, and they receive you, eat such things as are set before you. And heal the

10:17.620 --> 10:22.740
sick that are therein, and say unto them, The kingdom of God is come nigh unto you.

10:23.380 --> 10:29.380
But into whatsoever city ye enter, and they receive you not, go your ways out into the

10:29.380 --> 10:35.820
streets of the same, and say, Even the very dust of your city which cleaveth on us, we

10:35.820 --> 10:42.020
do wipe off against you. Notwithstanding be ye sure of this, that the kingdom of God is

10:42.020 --> 10:47.980
come nigh unto you. But I say unto you that it shall be more tolerable in that day for

10:47.980 --> 10:57.560
Sodom than for that city. Woe unto thee, Chorazin! Woe unto thee, Bethsaida! For if the mighty

10:57.560 --> 11:04.100
works had been done in Tyre and Sidon which have been done in you, they had a great while

11:04.100 --> 11:11.740
ago repented sitting in sackcloth and ashes. But it shall be more tolerable for Tyre and

11:11.740 --> 11:18.860
Sidon at the judgment than for you. And thou, Capernaum, which art exalted to heaven, shalt

11:18.860 --> 11:26.060
be thrust down to hell. He that heareth you heareth me, and he that despiseth you despiseth

11:26.580 --> 11:32.160
me, and he that despiseth me despiseth him that sent me.

11:32.940 --> 11:37.680
And the seven ye returned again with joy, saying, Lord, even the devils are subject

11:37.680 --> 11:44.140
unto us through thy name. And he said unto them, I beheld Satan as lightning fall from

11:44.140 --> 11:51.160
heaven. Behold, I give unto you power to tread on serpents and scorpions, and over all the

11:51.160 --> 11:57.920
power of the enemy, and nothing shall by any means hurt you. Notwithstanding in this rejoice

11:57.920 --> 12:03.760
not, that the spirits are subject unto you, but rather rejoice because your names are

12:03.760 --> 12:11.100
written in heaven. In that hour Jesus rejoiced in spirit and said, I thank thee, O Father,

12:11.300 --> 12:16.960
Lord of heaven and earth, that thou hast hid these things from the wise and prudent, and

12:16.960 --> 12:25.100
hast revealed them unto babes. Even so, Father, for so it seemed good in thy sight. All things

12:25.100 --> 12:31.540
are delivered to me of my Father, and no man knoweth who the Son is but the Father, and

12:31.540 --> 12:36.380
the Father is but the Son, and he to whom the Son will reveal him.

12:37.140 --> 12:42.860
And he turned him unto his disciples and said privately, Blessed are the eyes which see

12:42.860 --> 12:48.900
the things that ye see, for I tell you that many prophets and kings have desired to see

12:48.900 --> 12:55.080
those things which ye see, and have not seen them, and to hear those things which ye hear,

12:55.080 --> 13:02.520
and have not heard them. And behold a certain lawyer stood up and tempted him saying, Master,

13:02.640 --> 13:09.360
what shall I do to inherit eternal life? And he said unto him, What is written in the law?

13:10.160 --> 13:16.000
How readest thou? And he answering said, Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy

13:16.000 --> 13:21.880
heart and with all thy soul and with all thy strength and with all thy mind and thy neighbor

13:21.880 --> 13:29.600
as thyself. And he said unto him, Thou hast answered right, this do, and thou shalt live.

13:30.060 --> 13:36.940
But he, willing to justify himself, said unto Jesus, And who is my neighbor? And Jesus answering

13:36.940 --> 13:43.240
said, A certain man went down from Jerusalem to Jericho and fell among thieves which stripped

13:43.240 --> 13:49.600
him of his raiment and wounded him and departed, leaving him half dead. And by chance there

13:49.600 --> 13:55.740
came down a certain priest that way, and when he saw him he passed by on the other side.

13:56.660 --> 14:03.160
And likewise a Levite, when he was at the place, came and looked on him and passed by

14:03.160 --> 14:09.940
on the other side. But a certain Samaritan, as he journeyed, came where he was and when

14:09.940 --> 14:16.480
he saw him he had compassion on him, and went to him and bound up his wounds pouring in

14:16.480 --> 14:22.500
oil and wine, and set him on his own beast, and brought him to an inn and took care of

14:22.500 --> 14:28.340
him. And on the morrow when he departed he took out two pence and gave them to the host

14:28.340 --> 14:34.960
and said unto him, Take care of him and whatsoever thou spendest more, when I come again I will

14:34.960 --> 14:42.220
repay thee. Which now of these three thinkest thou was neighbor unto him that fell among

14:42.220 --> 14:50.660
the thieves. And he said, He that showed mercy on him. Then said Jesus unto him, Go and do

14:50.660 --> 14:55.900
thou likewise. Now it came to pass, as they went, that he entered into a certain village

14:55.900 --> 15:01.380
and a certain woman named Martha received him into her house. And she had a sister called

15:01.380 --> 15:07.760
Mary, which also sat at Jesus' feet and heard his word. But Martha was cumbered about,

15:07.760 --> 15:13.820
much serving, and came to him and said, Lord, dost thou not care that my sister hath left

15:13.820 --> 15:19.620
me to serve alone? Bid her therefore that she help me. And Jesus answered and said unto

15:19.620 --> 15:25.480
her, Martha, Martha, thou art careful and troubled about many things, but one thing

15:25.480 --> 15:32.440
is needful, and Mary hath chosen that good part which shall not be taken away from her.

15:46.600 --> 15:48.000
Amen.

